{"source_key":"sha256-ea08d35f42d5530fbe92c80d4f5b27e9","record_index":671,"record_hash":"sha256:e92350c3a009f1736df3008255dc371b953e8a01ccdbf8b1d7711365d1746111","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:45:23.016Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"**Lane 1 Finding: Pierre Helps, But It Doesn’t Remove Local Git**\\n\\nShort version: **code.storage can be a good remote/cache, but it does not solve the local filesystem requirement.** `git-meta-lib` / `but-agentlog` still need a local repo path.\\n\\nFindings:\\n\\n- **Public GitHub mirroring: yes.** Code Storage supports public GitHub sync without a GitHub App or GitHub credentials via `authType: 'public'`, then `pullUpstream()` refreshes from GitHub. Source: [Public GitHub Sync](https://code.[REDACTED:entropy]), [Git Sync docs](https://code.storage/docs/guides/integrations).\\n\\n- **Generic HTTPS Git sync: yes.** It supports syncing from GitLab, Bitbucket, Gitea, Forgejo, Codeberg, SourceHut, and similar hosts using HTTPS credentials. Source: [Generic HTTPS Git sync](https://code.storage/changelog/generic-https-git-sync), [Git Sync docs](https://code.storage/docs/guides/integrations).\\n\\n- **Git remote / Smart HTTP style access: yes.** Docs say Code Storage exposes native Git clone/push/fetch endpoints and `git clone`, `git fetch`, and `git pull` read from Code Storage once sync is configured. Source: [Code Storage homepage](https://code.storage/), [Git Sync docs](https://code.storage/docs/guides/integrations).\\n\\n- **Custom refs like `refs/meta/main`: unproven.** Docs prove repo sync and normal Git access, but I did not find an explicit guarantee that public GitHub sync mirrors arbitrary custom refs such as GitMeta’s `refs/meta/main`. We need a spike: create/sync a public repo with `refs/meta/main`, then `git ls-remote <code-storage-remote> 'refs/meta/*'`.\\n\\n- **Mounted filesystem access: no evidence.** I found API access, SDKs, Git remotes, archives, file APIs, and managed/self-hosted deployment language, but nothing suggesting FUSE/mount/local filesystem semantics.\\n\\nRecommendation: use Pierre/code.storage as an **upstream cache remote**, not as the Agent Trail execution substrate. The generator still needs a local scratch/bare repo on disk, fetches from GitHub or code.storage, hydrates GitMeta, then calls `but-agentlog`. So this still points toward a separate generator service unless Forge’s deployment gives us writable durable-ish disk, `git`, native addon loading, and enough runtime budget.\\n\\nI did not edit files.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:45:23.016Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}